<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,756,1001,1220]" pageId="78" pageNumber="393">
Possibly the largest genus of Spilomelinae, 
<taxonomicName box="[641,699,1001,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Udea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" subFamily="Spilomelinae">
<emphasis box="[641,699,1001,1024]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="393">Udea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now includes 214 species described from around the World (
<bibRefCitation author="Nuss M. &amp; Landry B. &amp; Vegliante F. &amp; Trankner A. &amp; Mally R. &amp; Hayden J. E. &amp; Bauer F. &amp; Segerer A. &amp; Li H. &amp; Schouten R. &amp; Solis M. A. &amp; Trofimova T. &amp; De Prins J. &amp; Speidel W." box="[159,341,1066,1091]" journalOrPublisher="Last accessed" pageId="78" pageNumber="393" pagination="2003 - 2016" part="1" refString="Nuss M., Landry B., Vegliante F., Trankner A., Mally R., Hayden J. E., Bauer F., Segerer A., Li H., Schouten R., Solis M. A., Trofimova T., De Prins J., Speidel W. 2003 - 2016. Global Information System on Pyraloidea. www. pyraloidea. org. Last accessed: 1 June 2016." title="Global Information System on Pyraloidea. www. pyraloidea. org" type="journal article" year="2016">
Nuss 
<emphasis box="[219,265,1066,1090]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="393">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). The fauna of the 
<collectingRegion box="[535,622,1067,1090]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="78" pageNumber="393">Western</collectingRegion>
Hemisphere is made up of 52 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Munroe E. G." box="[433,591,1098,1123]" editor="Heppner, J. B." journalOrPublisher="Hyblaeoidea - Pyraloidea - Tortricoidea" pageId="78" pageNumber="393" pagination="34 - 79" part="3" refString="Munroe E. G. 1995. Crambidae (Crambinae, Schoenobiinae, Cybalomiinae, Linostinae, Glaphyriinae, Dichogaminae, Scopariinae, Musotiminae, Midilinae, Nymphulinae, Odontiinae, Evergestinae, Pyraustinae). Pp. 34 - 79. In: Heppner, J. B., Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Checklist: Part 2. Hyblaeoidea - Pyraloidea - Tortricoidea 3. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera &amp; Scientific Publishers, Gainesville." title="Crambidae (Crambinae, Schoenobiinae, Cybalomiinae, Linostinae, Glaphyriinae, Dichogaminae, Scopariinae, Musotiminae, Midilinae, Nymphulinae, Odontiinae, Evergestinae, Pyraustinae). Pp" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Checklist: Part 2" year="1995">Munroe, 1995</bibRefCitation>
), excluding the two described as new below. All Neotropical species of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,241,1163,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Udea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="78" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" subFamily="Spilomelinae">
<emphasis box="[183,241,1163,1186]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="393">Udea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were checked to determine the two 
<collectingRegion box="[643,756,1163,1186]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="78" pageNumber="393">Galápagos</collectingRegion>
species as new.
</paragraph>
